**Key points:** Header is blockquote (`>`), sections use exact standard names, no numbering, Decisions table has 5 columns, all sections present.

## Format Compliance Checklist

Before writing a `.plan.md`, verify ALL of the following. The user and `/task-manager` reject non-compliant plans:

- [ ] **Plan log header** uses blockquote format (`> **Plan** | ...`), NOT a table
- [ ] **All header fields present:** Plan, Status, Priority, Created, Updated, Author, Environment, PR/Ticket, Rollback, Phase, Wave, Strategy Version, Active Tasks, Blocked Tasks
- [ ] **Section headings** use the exact names from "Plan Section Order" above — no numbering (`## 1. Overview` is wrong; `## Context` is correct), no renaming
- [ ] **All required sections present** — omit none; use "N/A" with justification if a section doesn't apply
- [ ] **Decisions table** present with `| # | Decision | Rationale | Date | Revisable? |` format
- [ ] **Success Criteria** section with measurable acceptance conditions
- [ ] **Open Questions** section for anything requiring user input

## Common Format Violations (NEVER do these)

- Using a markdown table for the plan header instead of blockquote format
- Numbering sections (`## 1. Overview`, `## 2. Architecture`) instead of using standard names
- Omitting sections (Decisions, Success Criteria, Resilience, Testing, Non-Goals, Risks & Rollback)
- Inventing custom section names not in the standard order
- Putting plan review notes or execution strategy inline instead of as appended sections

## Rules
- Always set status when creating or updating a plan
- Update the `Updated` date on every status change
- **Forward transitions:** Draft → In Review → Approved → In Progress → Completed
- **Backward transitions (allowed):** In Review → Draft (review feedback requires rework); In Progress → On Hold (blocker discovered)
- Update `Phase` when transitioning between workflow phases (Plan / Build / Review / Test / PR)
- Update `Wave` when advancing through execution waves (Wave 1, Wave 2, etc.) — set to `—` when not in Build phase
- `/check-progress` reads Phase and Wave to report current position
- Add PR/Ticket link once available
